This is a splendid beer.  I love drinking this nice, lovely delicious beer.

Its one of my favorites.

Functional, Ive drunk these for entire days and still managed to function.

Thats it, very non deScript.

you made me puke after a six pack when I was eighteen.

I will never forgive you for your transgression.

Fuck you, Camo 900.  Your previous products were downright nasty, and every one since has just been downright mean.

Theres absolutely nothing good about this product, how do you sleep with yourselves?

How can you accept yourselves as people?

Man, I need nothing more than 99 cents to remind me of former misery.  I would walk to my corner grocer and pick up a nice bottle of King Cobra.  Then Id drink it rather quickly and hope to pass in a puddle of my own sick.

God bless the Club.  Its a very delicious malt liqor with litte pretense and a subtle effect on my senses.

Theres nothing about this beer that should stop you from drinking a second one.  Its tasty and you should just accept it.

When cold, its crisp and easy.

Its just a very easy beer to drink on a summer day with a twelver at your side.

Its best to drink them fast as theres no flavor to inhibit you from going from one beer to another.

Please God, allow beers like this to continue to exist.  Its unfair that demonswill like Bud is allowed to exist, yet truly interesting cheap brews like Hamms arent as successful as they deserve to be.

Lets rise against Mickey Mouse beers and rediscover the beers of our forefathers.

A very mediocre European beer.  Ive drunk this many times in many locations with many different people.

If anyone were to tell me that this was superior to Hamms Id tell them to fuck off.

Fucking evil substance.  The kind of beer thatll leave you wishing you were dead and not lying in a puddle of your own sick at 3 in the morning.

I drank this and bore the pain of a three day hangover.  All from one can!

it had to have been this substance that did it, not the other drinks!

Ive drunk this one in Europe a couple of times.

Its nothing memorable for some reason.  Most of these lagers from Europe are no more memorable than a PBR or a Blatz or a Budweiser.

This is a fun beer.  All of the hype isnt what it deserves, but it is nonetheless a tasty brew.

Id take Pilsner Urquell over it any day.

Strangely, its a summer beer masquerading as a dark complex beer.  Slightly wonderful in all of its charms, Negra is still not that exciting in the flavor department, nor is it all that dissipointing.

Overall, I like drinking Negra, but dont do so that often.

Man, what a beer.  It was a really good time during that short period of time that I could get it.

I drank a twelver of it and then couldnt get it anymore.

My heart hurts when I see this label.  

It reminds me of the time when I could go to my neighborhood liquor store and buy my beer in returnable bottles.  The returnable bottles drove the cost of the beer down to absurd lows, I was paying 10 bucks for 24 in 2001!
Now its all changed.  Huber is hard to find and may come in a disposable bottle or can.  Huber products used to be inexpensive, delicious, and worth the investment.
Now that its all gone I feel as if Ive lost a true friend.
A beer pardner.

Oh, man, you dont remember this beer five years ago.  Back when it came in returnable bottles?
I used to get 24 for ten bucks from a liquor store in Chicago.  Then Id save the bottles and return them.  Those were the beauty times.
Now, it tastes kinda shitty.  The returnable bottles added a special flavor.

This was a hell of a beer, cant get it anymore.

Im bummed about that, you hear me, Ralphs????

Sorry, folks, Im not trying to be a cool guy with this one.  I genuinely love this beer.  I keep them very cold and I spend many an evening with them.

Its always a pleasure to crack one open at the end of a long, hard day.

Of course we have our times when we can afford more, but sometimes its just good to have something that reminds you of the times when your life wasnt so complicated.

This is a nice goddamned beer.  I drank maybe five of these in Belgium last year, one of the best experiences of my life.

Beauty.
This is a hell of a fun beer.  Ive drunk a bunch of this and its always a treasured experience.

This is a total memory beer for me.

I dont do anything to it, just pop it open and drink it...fast, enjoying its simple pleasures on my coordination.

Dude, this tastes like assyeast.

I cant call it anything else.  Its just purely offensive to drink.

I dont know, man.  I really can drink this stuff.  I dont know why, but this stuff is mad drinkable for me.  Its crazy, but I really like this nasty horsepiss of a beer.

Its five bucks for twelve and it works.
